claim: A rematch between The Rock and John Cena is scheduled for WrestleMania 29 .
truth: The match , and its year long buildup , was broadcast on NBC and later sent to DVD and Blu-Ray , collected under the title of The Rock vs John Cena : Once in a Lifetime. The match was later featured in WWE Best PPV Matches of 2012 as the Most Anticipated WrestleMania Match of All Time. A rematch is scheduled for WrestleMania 29.

claim: Less than 684,000 cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed .
truth: more than 683,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in approximately 32,100 deaths .

claim: According to the 2012 census , Mecklenburg County has a population of more than 950 thousand people .
truth: The population of Mecklenburg County is 969,031 people ( as of the 2012 census estimate ) , making it both the most populated and densely populated county in North Carolina .

claim: Before the upgrade , Wankhede Stadium 's capacity was over 70,000 .
truth: Before the upgrade , the capacity was approximately 90,000. The Wankhede stadium has been host to numerous high profile cricket matches in the past , most notable being the 2011 Cricket World Cup Final , in which India defeated Sri Lanka by 6 wickets .

claim: The F-19 is a hypothetical advanced fighter aircraft .
truth: F-19 is the designation for a hypothetical American advanced fighter aircraft that has never been officially acknowledged , and has engendered much speculation that it might refer to a type of aircraft whose existence is still classified.

claim: There are more than 703,500 cases of COVID-19 worldwide .
truth: more than 704,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in approximately 33,200 deaths .

claim: China had more than 9,500 confirmed coronavirus cases by January 30 , 2020 .
truth: As of 30 January 2020 , approximately 9,817 cases have been confirmed , including in every province-level division of China .

claim: New €100 and €200 banknotes were issued at the beginning of 2019 .
truth: The full design of the Europa series 50 euro note was revealed on 5 July 2016 and the new 50 note was released on 4 April 2017.New €50 banknote starts circulating todayThe new banknotes of the Europa series 100 euro banknote and 200 euro banknote will be issued at the beginning of 2019.New €50 banknote starts circulating todayOn 4 May 2016 , the European Central Bank announced that the Europa series 500 euro banknote would not be released , due to fears of `` facilitating the criminal activity '' .

claim: The state of Assam has confirmed a total of 29 positive cases of Covid-19 including 1 death after 11 April 2020 .
truth: The state has confirmed a total of 29 positive cases of Covid-19 including 1 death as of 12 April 2020.The cause of Covid-19 outbreak in Assam is due to the people who attended the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz and did not reported the authorities after their return to Assam .

claim: Nadine Coyle started recording songs for her sophomore studio album sometime in 2014 .
truth: Coyle , in August , also revealed she has been in the studio recording new songs for her forthcoming second studio album , most likely due in the middle of 2015.On 16 September 2014 , Coyle announced that she began working on her sophomore studio album with longtime collaborator Brian Higgins .

claim: There were more than 336,000 COVID-19 cases worldwide by March 23 , 2020 .
truth: As of 22 March , more than 335,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 14,600 deaths and 97,000 recoveries .

claim: Before May 2017 , Baby by Justin Bieber had over 1.59 billion views on YouTube .
truth: On March 5 , 2014 , `` Baby '' became the second video , after `` Gangnam Style '' , to receive 1 billion views on YouTube , and is the nineteenth most viewed video on the site , with over 1.59 billion views as of April 2017 .

claim: The urban subdivision of Reading had an estimated population of less than 250,000 according to the 2001 census .
truth: In the 2001 census , the urban sub-division of Reading had an estimated population of 232,662 , making it the largest town in the UK without city status .

claim: Chappie received more than 3 out of 5 stars from Time Out London , and Tom Huddleston stated that the film was odd but entertaining .
truth: Tom Huddleston of Time Out London rated it four out of five stars and wrote that `` this hugely entertaining oddity could never be mistaken for the work of any other filmmaker '' .

claim: The Youtube channel Epic Rap Battles of History has less than 13.3 million subscribers .
truth: As of May 2016 , it is the 20th most subscribed channel on YouTube with over 13.2 million subscribers and over 3 billion total video views .
